latestIgtvVideos.title: Man on a Mission.🥊
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I’ve always sincerely believed that being an actor requires more than just the art of acting. I’ve dedicated my time to external arts that has helped me to go on a personal journey of accomplishments. A few years ago, I took on gymnastics which was extremely challenging but by slowly mastering it, I learned to become a resilient artist. I learned to connect my mind with my body; learning control of movements of muscles in harmony with my thoughts. After my own satisfaction with gymnastics, I moved on to the next a new art. 
Few months back, I ventured on to mixed martial arts (MMA) and I cannot express how exhausting and challenging this journey has been. There were times when I wanted to give up especially when my teacher @thebruce5341 would literally beat the crap out me. Eventually after taking a few good punches, I learned to dodge them. This journey has been so intense and full of learning curves, but I always stood strong and honestly, never gave up because quitting has never been an option for me. Each physical obstacle required concentration and dedication to the art as it has helped me break through mental barriers as well. 
This skill has helped me get a little closer to becoming a better actor. 
I’ve never believed in a one sided approach to growth, so I wanted to share my journey with you guys. I want to thank my trainer for all the love and support your the BEST @thebruce5341 without ur punches and kicks this would have not been possible ..
And special thanks to @i_mohsin_ahmed  to motivate me and be a amazing friend forever

This would have not been possible without @theflexstudio_mumbai 🥊🥊
